This paper deals with the task of determining author intent from multimodal data, specifically Instagram posts. This involves modeling the complex relationship between text and image, which falls under the sub-category of natural language processing (NLP) and multimodal learning. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.MM (Multimedia) are the most likely sub-categories. 

The paper also involves classification tasks, which can fall under several sub-categories such as information retrieval (cs.IR), computer vision (cs.CV), and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of deep learning models for classification also suggests cs.LG as a likely sub-category.
